Hangman Server and Client in Python

Instructions:

To run locally without Google App Engine (GAE):
- Download and install MySQL
http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/
- Start server and connect to mysql client
mysql -u root -p
- Create database
create database hangman
- Create tables
Run SQL commands under database/ to create required tables.
- Install CherryPy
pip install cherrypy
- Install Jinja2
pip install Jinja2
- Install MySQLdb
pip install MySQL-python
- Run server
python server/server.py
- Install gflags
pip install python-gflags
- Run client
python client/client.py
It will play the game for 10 times and return the result.

To run locally with Google App Engine (GAE):
- Install GAE by downloading from the official website
- Install CherryPy and other libraries
Mac:
pip install --install-option="--prefix=" -t lib -r requirements.txt
Linux:
pip install -t lib -r requirements.txt
- Run server
dev_appserver.py .
- Run client
python client/client.py
It will play the game for 10 times and return the result.

To run server on Google App Engine (GAE):
- Install GAE by downloading from the official website
- Install CherryPy and other libraries
Mac:
pip install --install-option="--prefix=" -t lib -r requirements.txt
Linux:
pip install -t lib -r requirements.txt
- Setup your GAE, and create a project
- Push code to GAE
appcfg.py -A <YOUR_PROJECT_ID_> update .
- Change client.py to point to the GAE server
- Run client
python client/client.py
It will play the game for 10 times and return the result.

References:
- MySQL:
- CherryPy: http://www.cherrypy.org/
- Jinja2: http://jinja.pocoo.org/docs/dev/
- Bootstrap: http://getbootstrap.com/
